Former Chairman of Pension Reform Taskforce, Abdul-Rasheed Maina, was on Friday arraigned by the Federal government on a 12-count corruption charge before Justice Okon Abang of the Abuja division of the Federal High Court. The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission (EFCC) in the 12-count charge had accused Maina of corruption and money laundering when he was at the helms of affairs of the reform team. He however pleaded not guilty to all the 12-count charge. Details laterâ€¦